<item>
            <title>[HBASE-11] [hbase] Unexpected exits corrupt DFS</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-11</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a RegionServer exits unexpectedly, it often leaves its DFS files open. In the case of the redo log, this can result in a zero-length file, which a newly started RegionServer will be unable to read, causing it to exit again. It also causes DFS corruption, requiring the admin to run a dfs fsck -delete before HBase can be restarted.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12387516">HBASE-11</key>
            <summary>[hbase] Unexpected exits corrupt DFS</summary>
